cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

The paper focuses on developing a framework for feature learning in neuromorphic vision sensing, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also utilizes graph convolution neural networks, which are a popular tool in the field of deep learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also proposes a novel end-to-end feature learning framework, which involves both appearance-based and motion-based tasks, indicating that it may fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of neuromorphic action recognition datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.RO (Robotics).
